  <sect1 id="event-trigger-interface">
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=9aef50b887f11c8d6db98cd77d28ab26 sig_cn_org=None source=14.1 
   <title>Writing Event Trigger Functions in C</title>
________________________________________________________-->
   <title>用 C 编写事件触发器函数</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=9aef50b887f11c8d6db98cd77d28ab26 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=a2681961f38fa32299eb7873103f1129 sig_cn_org=None source=14.1 
   <indexterm zone="event-trigger-interface">
    <primary>event trigger</primary>
    <secondary>in C</secondary>
   </indexterm>
________________________________________________________-->
   <indexterm zone="event-trigger-interface">
    <primary>event trigger</primary>
    <secondary>in C</secondary>
   </indexterm>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=a2681961f38fa32299eb7873103f1129 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=028ea5c16188b2edd2768bbf46a8699a sig_cn_org=None source=14.1 
   <para>
    This section describes the low-level details of the interface to an
    event trigger function. This information is only needed when writing
    event trigger functions in C. If you are using a higher-level language
    then these details are handled for you. In most cases you should
    consider using a procedural language before writing your event triggers
    in C. The documentation of each procedural language explains how to
    write an event trigger in that language.
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    这一节描述了事件触发器函数接口的低层细节。只有在用 C 编写事件
    触发器函数时才需要用到这里的信息。如果使用更高层的语言，那么
    这些细节已经被处理好了。在大部分情况下都应该优先考虑使用过程
    语言来编写你的事件触发器。每一种过程语言的文档都解释了如何用
    它编写事件触发器。
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=028ea5c16188b2edd2768bbf46a8699a -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=d36702320a707e73dabb3c5f1a393bac sig_cn_org=None source=14.1 
   <para>
    Event trigger functions must use the <quote>version 1</quote> function
    manager interface.
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    事件触发器函数必须使用<quote>版本 1</quote>的函数管理器接口。
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=d36702320a707e73dabb3c5f1a393bac -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=5f2eb3be7afb91029a3173193e598d34 sig_cn_org=None source=14.1 
   <para>
    When a function is called by the event trigger manager, it is not passed
    any normal arguments, but it is passed a <quote>context</quote> pointer
    pointing to a <structname>EventTriggerData</structname> structure. C functions can
    check whether they were called from the event trigger manager or not by
    executing the macro:
<programlisting>
CALLED_AS_EVENT_TRIGGER(fcinfo)
</programlisting>
    which expands to:
<programlisting>
((fcinfo)-&gt;context != NULL &amp;&amp; IsA((fcinfo)-&gt;context, EventTriggerData))
</programlisting>
    If this returns true, then it is safe to cast
    <literal>fcinfo-&gt;context</literal> to type <literal>EventTriggerData
    *</literal> and make use of the pointed-to
    <structname>EventTriggerData</structname> structure.  The function must
    <emphasis>not</emphasis> alter the <structname>EventTriggerData</structname>
    structure or any of the data it points to.
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    当一个函数被事件触发器管理器调用时，向它传递的并不是普通参数，
    而是一个指向<structname>EventTriggerData</structname>结构的
    <quote>context</quote>指针。C 函数可以通过执行以下宏来检查它是否
    被事件触发器管理器调用：
<programlisting>
CALLED_AS_EVENT_TRIGGER(fcinfo)
</programlisting>
    这个宏会被扩展为：
<programlisting>
((fcinfo)-&gt;context != NULL &amp;&amp; IsA((fcinfo)-&gt;context, EventTriggerData))
</programlisting>
    如果这个宏返回真，那么就可以安全地把
    <literal>fcinfo-&gt;context</literal>造型为类型<literal>EventTriggerData
    *</literal>并且使用所指向的<structname>EventTriggerData</structname>结构。
    函数<emphasis>不能</emphasis>修改
    <structname>EventTriggerData</structname>结构以及它指向的任何内容。
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=5f2eb3be7afb91029a3173193e598d34 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=48a0793bd6316a1f34f9b8dc5fd0c968 sig_cn_org=850f70840b9bd0d8018ffbbc49571453 source=17.5 
   <para>
    <structname>struct EventTriggerData</structname> is defined in
    <filename>commands/event_trigger.h</filename>:

<programlisting>
typedef struct EventTriggerData
{
    NodeTag     type;
    const char *event;      /* event name */
    Node       *parsetree;  /* parse tree */
    CommandTag  tag;        /* command tag */
} EventTriggerData;
</programlisting>

    where the members are defined as follows:

    <variablelist>
     <varlistentry>
      <term><structfield>type</structfield></term>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Always <literal>T_EventTriggerData</literal>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </varlistentry>

     <varlistentry>
      <term><structfield>event</structfield></term>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Describes the event for which the function is called, one of
        <literal>"login"</literal>, <literal>"ddl_command_start"</literal>,
        <literal>"ddl_command_end"</literal>, <literal>"sql_drop"</literal>,
        <literal>"table_rewrite"</literal>.
        See <xref linkend="event-trigger-definition"/> for the meaning of these
        events.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </varlistentry>

     <varlistentry>
      <term><structfield>parsetree</structfield></term>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        A pointer to the parse tree of the command.  Check the PostgreSQL
        source code for details.  The parse tree structure is subject to change
        without notice.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </varlistentry>

     <varlistentry>
      <term><structfield>tag</structfield></term>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        The command tag associated with the event for which the event trigger
        is run, for example <literal>"CREATE FUNCTION"</literal>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    <structname>struct EventTriggerData</structname> 定义在
    <filename>commands/event_trigger.h</filename>：

<programlisting>
typedef struct EventTriggerData
{
    NodeTag     type;
    const char *event;      /* event name */
    Node       *parsetree;  /* parse tree */
    CommandTag  tag;        /* command tag */
} EventTriggerData;
</programlisting>

    其成员定义如下：

    <variablelist>
     <varlistentry>
      <term><structfield>type</structfield></term>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        始终为 <literal>T_EventTriggerData</literal>。
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </varlistentry>

     <varlistentry>
      <term><structfield>event</structfield></term>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        描述函数被调用的事件，可能是 <literal>"login"</literal>、
        <literal>"ddl_command_start"</literal>、<literal>"ddl_command_end"</literal>、
        <literal>"sql_drop"</literal>、<literal>"table_rewrite"</literal> 中的一个。
        详见 <xref linkend="event-trigger-definition"/> 了解这些事件的含义。
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </varlistentry>

     <varlistentry>
      <term><structfield>parsetree</structfield></term>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        指向命令解析树的指针。详情请查看 PostgreSQL 源代码。解析树结构
        可能会在无通知的情况下发生变化。
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </varlistentry>

     <varlistentry>
      <term><structfield>tag</structfield></term>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        与事件触发器运行的事件相关联的命令标签，例如
        <literal>"CREATE FUNCTION"</literal>。
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=48a0793bd6316a1f34f9b8dc5fd0c968 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=ef5e541b842a6c21b6c5a219510c7f4c sig_cn_org=None source=14.1 
   <para>
    An event trigger function must return a <symbol>NULL</symbol> pointer
    (<emphasis>not</emphasis> an SQL null value, that is, do not
    set <parameter>isNull</parameter> true).
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    一个事件触发器函数必须返回一个<symbol>NULL</symbol>指针（
    <emphasis>不是</emphasis>一个 SQL 空值，也就是不要把
    <parameter>isNull</parameter>设置为 true）。
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=ef5e541b842a6c21b6c5a219510c7f4c -->
  </sect1>

  <sect1 id="event-trigger-example">
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=d2754e3bcbacedcd0c59cdf5193f917e sig_cn_org=None source=14.1 
   <title>A Complete Event Trigger Example</title>
________________________________________________________-->
   <title>一个完整的事件触发器示例</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=d2754e3bcbacedcd0c59cdf5193f917e -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=165930c0d6b9409863eecd7ecf0cfa8b sig_cn_org=None source=14.1 
   <para>
    Here is a very simple example of an event trigger function written in C.
    (Examples of triggers written in procedural languages can be found in
    the documentation of the procedural languages.)
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    这里是一个用 C 编写的事件触发器函数的简单例子（用过程语言编写的触发器
    例子可以在过程语言的文档中找到）。
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=165930c0d6b9409863eecd7ecf0cfa8b -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=3e944a3b2660e040288726fd33cd2250 sig_cn_org=None source=14.1 
   <para>
    The function <function>noddl</function> raises an exception each time it is called.
    The event trigger definition associated the function with
    the <literal>ddl_command_start</literal> event.  The effect is that all DDL
    commands (with the exceptions mentioned
    in <xref linkend="event-trigger-definition"/>) are prevented from running.
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    函数<function>noddl</function>在每一次被调用时抛出一个异常。
    事件触发器定义把该函数和
    <literal>ddl_command_start</literal>事件关联在了一起。其效果就是所有
    DDL 命令（除<xref linkend="event-trigger-definition"/>中提到的例外）都
    被阻止运行。
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=3e944a3b2660e040288726fd33cd2250 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=fd9bf1b74336fbb4c670661546d1a7d1 sig_cn_org=3deb787b3c550886c67ca316908be9f2 source=17.5 
   <para>
    This is the source code of the trigger function:
<programlisting><![CDATA[
#include "postgres.h"

#include "commands/event_trigger.h"
#include "fmgr.h"

PG_MODULE_MAGIC;

PG_FUNCTION_INFO_V1(noddl);

Datum
noddl(PG_FUNCTION_ARGS)
{
    EventTriggerData *trigdata;

    if (!CALLED_AS_EVENT_TRIGGER(fcinfo))  /* internal error */
        elog(ERROR, "not fired by event trigger manager");

    trigdata = (EventTriggerData *) fcinfo->context;

    ereport(ERROR,
            (errcode(ERRCODE_INSUFFICIENT_PRIVILEGE),
             errmsg("command \"%s\" denied",
                    GetCommandTagName(trigdata->tag))));

    PG_RETURN_NULL();
}
]]></programlisting>
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    这是触发器函数的源代码：
<programlisting><![CDATA[
#include "postgres.h"

#include "commands/event_trigger.h"
#include "fmgr.h"

PG_MODULE_MAGIC;

PG_FUNCTION_INFO_V1(noddl);

Datum
noddl(PG_FUNCTION_ARGS)
{
    EventTriggerData *trigdata;

    if (!CALLED_AS_EVENT_TRIGGER(fcinfo))  /* internal error */
        elog(ERROR, "not fired by event trigger manager");

    trigdata = (EventTriggerData *) fcinfo->context;

    ereport(ERROR,
            (errcode(ERRCODE_INSUFFICIENT_PRIVILEGE),
             errmsg("command \"%s\" denied",
                    GetCommandTagName(trigdata->tag))));

    PG_RETURN_NULL();
}
]]></programlisting>
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=fd9bf1b74336fbb4c670661546d1a7d1 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=046cd841de1f4b97c67b2aa26f6e0a94 sig_cn_org=None source=14.1 
   <para>
    After you have compiled the source code (see <xref linkend="dfunc"/>),
    declare the function and the triggers:
<programlisting>
CREATE FUNCTION noddl() RETURNS event_trigger
    AS 'noddl' LANGUAGE C;

CREATE EVENT TRIGGER noddl ON ddl_command_start
    EXECUTE FUNCTION noddl();
</programlisting>
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    在编译了源代码（见<xref linkend="dfunc"/>）后，
    声明函数和触发器：
<programlisting>
CREATE FUNCTION noddl() RETURNS event_trigger
    AS 'noddl' LANGUAGE C;

CREATE EVENT TRIGGER noddl ON ddl_command_start
    EXECUTE FUNCTION noddl();
</programlisting>
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=046cd841de1f4b97c67b2aa26f6e0a94 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=9bbca6e04a8f54992b35a58d2932a1f3 sig_cn_org=None source=14.1 
   <para>
    Now you can test the operation of the trigger:
<screen>
=# \dy
                     List of event triggers
 Name  |       Event       | Owner | Enabled | Function | Tags
-&minus;-&minus;-&minus;-+-&minus;-&minus;-&minus;-&minus;-&minus;-&minus;-&minus;-&minus;-&minus;-+-&minus;-&minus;-&minus;-+-&minus;-&minus;-&minus;-&minus;-+-&minus;-&minus;-&minus;-&minus;-&minus;+-&minus;-&minus;-&minus;
 noddl | ddl_command_start | dim   | enabled | noddl    |
(1 row)

=# CREATE TABLE foo(id serial);
ERROR:  command "CREATE TABLE" denied
</screen>
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    现在你可以测试该触发器的操作：
<screen>
=# \dy
                     List of event triggers
 Name  |       Event       | Owner | Enabled | Function | Tags
-------+-------------------+-------+---------+----------+------
 noddl | ddl_command_start | dim   | enabled | noddl    |
(1 row)

=# CREATE TABLE foo(id serial);
ERROR:  command "CREATE TABLE" denied
</screen>
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=9bbca6e04a8f54992b35a58d2932a1f3 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=81bbd0634059614e7f2e659bf93a6c69 sig_cn_org=None source=14.1 
   <para>
    In this situation, in order to be able to run some DDL commands when you
    need to do so, you have to either drop the event trigger or disable it.  It
    can be convenient to disable the trigger for only the duration of a
    transaction:
<programlisting>
BEGIN;
ALTER EVENT TRIGGER noddl DISABLE;
CREATE TABLE foo (id serial);
ALTER EVENT TRIGGER noddl ENABLE;
COMMIT;
</programlisting>
    (Recall that DDL commands on event triggers themselves are not affected by
    event triggers.)
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    在这种情况下，为了在需要时能运行某些 DDL 命令，你必须删除该事件触发器
    或者禁用它。只在一个事务期间禁用该触发器会比较方便：
<programlisting>
BEGIN;
ALTER EVENT TRIGGER noddl DISABLE;
CREATE TABLE foo (id serial);
ALTER EVENT TRIGGER noddl ENABLE;
COMMIT;
</programlisting>
    （回忆一下，事件触发器本身上的 DDL 命令不受事件触发器影响）。
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=81bbd0634059614e7f2e659bf93a6c69 -->
  </sect1>

  <sect1 id="event-trigger-table-rewrite-example">
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=32379c4351547aed8dc4da4ea0869af5 sig_cn_org=None source=14.1 
   <title>A Table Rewrite Event Trigger Example</title>
________________________________________________________-->
   <title>一个表重写事件触发器示例</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=32379c4351547aed8dc4da4ea0869af5 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=1c3f370fd5932e548f4a50182d7278d2 sig_cn_org=None source=14.1 
   <para>
    Thanks to the <literal>table_rewrite</literal> event, it is possible to implement
    a table rewriting policy only allowing the rewrite in maintenance windows.
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    得益于<literal>table_rewrite</literal>事件的存在，我们可以实现一种只允许在
    维护窗口中重写的表重写策略。
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=1c3f370fd5932e548f4a50182d7278d2 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=2cb3bd06497a3a11804c68c93316a5e0 sig_cn_org=None source=14.1 
   <para>
    Here's an example implementing such a policy.
<programlisting>
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION no_rewrite()
 RETURNS event_trigger
 LANGUAGE plpgsql AS
$$
-&minus;-
-&minus;- Implement local Table Rewriting policy:
-&minus;-   public.foo is not allowed rewriting, ever
-&minus;-   other tables are only allowed rewriting between 1am and 6am
-&minus;-   unless they have more than 100 blocks
-&minus;-
DECLARE
  table_oid oid := pg_event_trigger_table_rewrite_oid();
  current_hour integer := extract('hour' from current_time);
  pages integer;
  max_pages integer := 100;
BEGIN
  IF pg_event_trigger_table_rewrite_oid() = 'public.foo'::regclass
  THEN
        RAISE EXCEPTION 'you''re not allowed to rewrite the table %',
                        table_oid::regclass;
  END IF;

  SELECT INTO pages relpages FROM pg_class WHERE oid = table_oid;
  IF pages > max_pages
  THEN
        RAISE EXCEPTION 'rewrites only allowed for table with less than % pages',
                        max_pages;
  END IF;

  IF current_hour NOT BETWEEN 1 AND 6
  THEN
        RAISE EXCEPTION 'rewrites only allowed between 1am and 6am';
  END IF;
END;
$$;

CREATE EVENT TRIGGER no_rewrite_allowed
                  ON table_rewrite
   EXECUTE FUNCTION no_rewrite();
</programlisting>
   </para>
________________________________________________________-->
   <para>
    这里是实现这种策略的例子。
<programlisting>
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION no_rewrite()
 RETURNS event_trigger
 LANGUAGE plpgsql AS
$$
---
--- 实现本地表重写策略：
---   public.foo 不允许重写，其他表只允许在 1am 和 6am 之间重写，
---   且前提是它们拥有不超过 100 块
---
DECLARE
table_oid oid := pg_event_trigger_table_rewrite_oid();
  current_hour integer := extract('hour' from current_time);
  pages integer;
  max_pages integer := 100;
  BEGIN
IF pg_event_trigger_table_rewrite_oid() = 'public.foo'::regclass
  THEN
  RAISE EXCEPTION 'you''re not allowed to rewrite the table %',
        table_oid::regclass;
                        END IF;
  
SELECT INTO pages relpages FROM pg_class WHERE oid = table_oid;
  IF pages > max_pages
  THEN
  RAISE EXCEPTION 'rewrites only allowed for table with less than % pages',
        max_pages;
                        END IF;
  
IF current_hour NOT BETWEEN 1 AND 6
  THEN
  RAISE EXCEPTION 'rewrites only allowed between 1am and 6am';
        END IF;
  END;
$$;

CREATE EVENT TRIGGER no_rewrite_allowed
ON table_rewrite
                  EXECUTE FUNCTION no_rewrite();
   </programlisting>
   </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=2cb3bd06497a3a11804c68c93316a5e0 -->
 </sect1>

  <sect1 id="event-trigger-database-login-example">
<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=665b49884bbf1d99902cb7d17bdb696f sig_cn_org=400d4a0cc777981da040e0e0d8b26b05 source=17.5 
    <title>A Database Login Event Trigger Example</title>
________________________________________________________-->
    <title>数据库登录事件触发器示例</title>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=665b49884bbf1d99902cb7d17bdb696f -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=afc7e02fbc5cf6d4960888f34c6e1227 sig_cn_org=bf3d00d51f9cf5e1c844396ec8254b2c source=17.5 
    <para>
      The event trigger on the <literal>login</literal> event can be
      useful for logging user logins, for verifying the connection and
      assigning roles according to current circumstances, or for session
      data initialization. It is very important that any event trigger using
      the <literal>login</literal> event checks whether or not the database is
      in recovery before performing any writes. Writing to a standby server
      will make it inaccessible.
    </para>
________________________________________________________-->
    <para>
      触发<literal>login</literal>事件的事件触发器对于记录用户登录、验证连接、
      根据当前情况分配角色或初始化会话数据非常有用。非常重要的是，任何使用
      <literal>login</literal>事件的事件触发器在执行写操作之前都必须检查数据库
      是否处于恢复状态。写入备用服务器将导致其无法访问。
    </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=afc7e02fbc5cf6d4960888f34c6e1227 -->

<!-- pgdoc-cn_start sig_en=c44b4a64d06f5fa427367c015d639230 sig_cn_org=cc59af3b5428a1b70a320255f55de4b1 source=17.5 
    <para>
      The following example demonstrates these options.
<programlisting>
-&minus; create test tables and roles
CREATE TABLE user_login_log (
  "user" text,
  "session_start" timestamp with time zone
);
CREATE ROLE day_worker;
CREATE ROLE night_worker;

-&minus; the example trigger function
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION init_session()
  RETURNS event_trigger SECURITY DEFINER
  LANGUAGE plpgsql AS
$$
DECLARE
  hour integer = EXTRACT('hour' FROM current_time at time zone 'utc');
  rec boolean;
BEGIN
-&minus; 1. Forbid logging in between 2AM and 4AM.
IF hour BETWEEN 2 AND 4 THEN
  RAISE EXCEPTION 'Login forbidden';
END IF;

-&minus; The checks below cannot be performed on standby servers so
-&minus; ensure the database is not in recovery before we perform any
-&minus; operations.
SELECT pg_is_in_recovery() INTO rec;
IF rec THEN
  RETURN;
END IF;

-&minus; 2. Assign some roles. At daytime, grant the day_worker role, else the
-&minus; night_worker role.
IF hour BETWEEN 8 AND 20 THEN
  EXECUTE 'REVOKE night_worker FROM ' || quote_ident(session_user);
  EXECUTE 'GRANT day_worker TO ' || quote_ident(session_user);
ELSE
  EXECUTE 'REVOKE day_worker FROM ' || quote_ident(session_user);
  EXECUTE 'GRANT night_worker TO ' || quote_ident(session_user);
END IF;

-&minus; 3. Initialize user session data
CREATE TEMP TABLE session_storage (x float, y integer);
ALTER TABLE session_storage OWNER TO session_user;

-&minus; 4. Log the connection time
INSERT INTO public.user_login_log VALUES (session_user, current_timestamp);

END;
$$;

-&minus; trigger definition
CREATE EVENT TRIGGER init_session
  ON login
  EXECUTE FUNCTION init_session();
ALTER EVENT TRIGGER init_session ENABLE ALWAYS;
</programlisting>
    </para>
________________________________________________________-->
    <para>
      以下示例演示了这些选项。
<programlisting>
-- create test tables and roles
CREATE TABLE user_login_log (
  "user" text,
  "session_start" timestamp with time zone
);
CREATE ROLE day_worker;
CREATE ROLE night_worker;

-- the example trigger function
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION init_session()
  RETURNS event_trigger SECURITY DEFINER
  LANGUAGE plpgsql AS
$$
DECLARE
  hour integer = EXTRACT('hour' FROM current_time at time zone 'utc');
  rec boolean;
BEGIN
-- 1. Forbid logging in between 2AM and 4AM.
IF hour BETWEEN 2 AND 4 THEN
  RAISE EXCEPTION 'Login forbidden';
END IF;

-- The checks below cannot be performed on standby servers so
-- ensure the database is not in recovery before we perform any
-- operations.
SELECT pg_is_in_recovery() INTO rec;
IF rec THEN
  RETURN;
END IF;

-- 2. Assign some roles. At daytime, grant the day_worker role, else the
-- night_worker role.
IF hour BETWEEN 8 AND 20 THEN
  EXECUTE 'REVOKE night_worker FROM ' || quote_ident(session_user);
  EXECUTE 'GRANT day_worker TO ' || quote_ident(session_user);
ELSE
  EXECUTE 'REVOKE day_worker FROM ' || quote_ident(session_user);
  EXECUTE 'GRANT night_worker TO ' || quote_ident(session_user);
END IF;

-- 3. Initialize user session data
CREATE TEMP TABLE session_storage (x float, y integer);
ALTER TABLE session_storage OWNER TO session_user;

-- 4. Log the connection time
INSERT INTO public.user_login_log VALUES (session_user, current_timestamp);

END;
$$;

-- trigger definition
CREATE EVENT TRIGGER init_session
  ON login
  EXECUTE FUNCTION init_session();
ALTER EVENT TRIGGER init_session ENABLE ALWAYS;
</programlisting>
    </para>
<!-- pgdoc-cn_end sig_en=c44b4a64d06f5fa427367c015d639230 -->
  </sect1>
</chapter>
